in 2004, the company entered
into commutation agreements with a major reinsurer, resulting in a charge of
$153 million for amounts received less than the reinsurance recoverable
balances of approximately $1.26 billion. in connection with the commutation,
the company also entered into a new reinsurance agreement effective april1,
