stock option fair value information
the fair value effect of stock options is derived by
application of a variation of the black-scholes option pricing model.
the significant assumptions used in estimating the
fair value on the date of the grant for original options and reload options
granted in 2005, 2004 and 2003 and for the awards assumed on april 1, 2004 from
spc at the merger were as follows:
